Text.Value: I know what you did to your son. I know you sold him into slavery.
You're Gortash's father, then?
Probe his mind.
This man is nothing more than a puppet now. Put him out of his misery.
Nothing untoward about it, I assure you.
*Nothing. It's as though the inner workings of his mind have been wiped clean.*
You're Gortash's father, then?
You've got the wrong family. Enver's the light of our lives. He grew up right in these walls - first my apprentice, then saviour of the city, and on to Archduke.
Our son - our beautiful boy, Enver, has been killed. Right before his prime. He was meant to be the Archduke, you know. Such senseless violence.
Leave.
Connect your tadpole to his.
He's the image of me, isn't he? Always was a handsome devil.
*You delve into his mind and find... nothing. Like someone or something has drained his mind of all personality.*
Gortash's dad. And he seems... proud.
Be very welcome to Flymm's Cobblers! Humble family home of our soon-to-be Archduke Enver Gortash!
He may not have followed in his old man's shoe-steps, but Archduke's not so bad, is it?
Very good to see you again!
We're closed for business today. Apologies.
What are you doing?! Stop that right now!
Gortash's dad. Same treatment as his mum, I guess.
Let me see your wares.
*You focus on the source of the power, but it is quiet and still. It needs to rest.*
Goodness, what an accusation!
Be very welcome to Flymm's Cobblers! Humble family home of our Archduke Enver Gortash!
Finest leather in the city - ask anyone!
Begging your pardon.
Wh-what are you doing?
He was the image of me. And the best of me. Everything he accomplished... Gods, he made us so proud.

Synopsis: Default dialogue for Gortash's father, Dravo Flymm, at Flymm Cobblers in the Lower City. Gortash tadpoled his parents, who sold him into slavery in his youth. They are aware of their state but cannot resist the tadpole's compulsion - which makes them appear as huge fans of their son.
